{
  "stem": "12289.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh no, that-- that-- that was not-- [LAUGHS] It-- it, of course, was interesting in a way.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But there were more important tasks now for me, and that-- that was to save peoples' lives.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was my job, to join the Raoul Wallenberg sort of mission in a way.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You see, this is interesting to see how a small embassy-- we were five people, my boss, myself, a chancellery officer, a driver, two girls, that was the whole.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and we asked for more staff.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Raoul Wallenberg came.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We got some other helpers, also. --how that grew into an-- an enormous organization, with me sitting in the center to try to coordinate all this.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was the Raoul Wallenberg very, very important mission, action, with all these offices and all that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had the Swedish Red Cross, who was working along the same lines as Raoul Wallenberg but on a much smaller scale.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had a Save the Children, a-- a-- a-- a rather old lady at the time, who came also to our help and were organizing a children's home for Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You had a big section for all the interests we had under the countries.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know, during the war, at the war-- at the wartime, the neutrals, like during the First World War and after-- and also during the Second World War, Switzerland and Sweden more or less divided the world in two, so to say.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we had in Budapest-- the-- the Swiss had the British, the Americans, and all these interests.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You can't keep your embassies, as you understand, in your enemy city.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we took over other embassies.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We took over the Dutch and the Finnish and the-- many of these.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
